# ScrapCo V2 — API Specification

## 1. API Philosophy

The API layer must be:

- Stateless
- Role-aware
- Strictly validated
- Idempotent
- Event-driven
- Versioned
- Horizontally scalable

No business-critical logic must depend on memory state.

All endpoints must:
- Validate input via Zod
- Enforce JWT authentication
- Enforce role-based access
- Return standardized response structure

---

## 2. Base Configuration

Base URL:

```

[https://api.scrapco.app/v1](https://api.scrapco.app/v1)

```

Versioning required:

```

/v1/

````

---

## 3. Standard Response Format

### Success

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {},
  "meta": {}
}
````

### Error

```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": {
    "code": "ERROR_CODE",
    "message": "Human readable message"
  }
}
```

No raw error responses allowed.

---

## 4. Authentication

### Auth Type

* Supabase JWT (Bearer Token)

Header:

```
Authorization: Bearer <jwt>
```

Vendor webhooks:

* HMAC signature required

---

## 5. Health Check

### GET /v1/health

Response:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "status": "ok",
    "database": "connected",
    "redis": "connected"
  }
}
```

---

# 6. Seller Endpoints

---

## 6.1 Create Pickup

### POST /v1/pickups

Role: SELLER

Body:

```json
{
  "regionId": "uuid",
  "scheduledAt": "ISO_DATE",
  "latitude": 0,
  "longitude": 0,
  "items": [
    {
      "scrapTypeId": "uuid",
      "estimatedQuantity": 10
    }
  ]
}
```

Response:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "pickupId": "uuid",
    "status": "PENDING"
  }
}
```

Action:

* Insert pickup
* Insert pickup_items
* Enqueue dispatch job
* Emit PickupCreated event

---

## 6.2 Get Pickup Details

### GET /v1/pickups/:id

Role: SELLER or ASSIGNED VENDOR or ADMIN

Response:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "pickup": {},
    "items": [],
    "assignment": {},
    "transaction": {}
  }
}
```

---

## 6.3 Cancel Pickup

### POST /v1/pickups/:id/cancel

Role: SELLER

Conditions:

* Cannot cancel if COMPLETED

Response:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "status": "CANCELLED"
  }
}
```

Audit log required.

---

# 7. Vendor Endpoints

---

## 7.1 Get Assigned Pickups

### GET /v1/vendor/pickups

Role: VENDOR

Response:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": [
    {}
  ]
}
```

---

## 7.2 Accept Offer

### POST /v1/vendor/offers/:offerId/accept

Role: VENDOR

Validation:

* Offer must belong to vendor
* Not expired
* Not already accepted

Response:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "status": "ASSIGNED"
  }
}
```

Actions:

* Update offer
* Create assignment
* Update pickup status
* Emit VendorOfferAccepted

---

## 7.3 Reject Offer

### POST /v1/vendor/offers/:offerId/reject

Role: VENDOR

Response:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "status": "REJECTED"
  }
}
```

Dispatch job for next vendor.

---

## 7.4 Update Vendor Location

### POST /v1/vendor/location

Role: VENDOR

Body:

```json
{
  "latitude": 0,
  "longitude": 0
}
```

Must require JWT.
No public write endpoint allowed.

---

# 8. Admin Endpoints

---

## 8.1 Create Scrap Type

### POST /v1/admin/scrap-types

Role: ADMIN

Body:

```json
{
  "name": "Plastic"
}
```

---

## 8.2 Set Scrap Rate

### POST /v1/admin/scrap-rates

Role: ADMIN

Body:

```json
{
  "scrapTypeId": "uuid",
  "regionId": "uuid",
  "ratePerKg": 25
}
```

Must deactivate previous active rate.

---

## 8.3 Get Region Metrics

### GET /v1/admin/regions/:id/metrics

Role: ADMIN

Returns:

```json
{
  "totalPickups": 0,
  "completedPickups": 0,
  "revenue": 0,
  "vendorAcceptanceRate": 0
}
```

---

# 9. Worker/Internal Endpoints (Private)

These must not be public.

### POST /internal/dispatch/process

Only accessible by worker service.

---

# 10. Webhook Endpoints

Vendor HMAC required.

---

## 10.1 Vendor Accept Webhook

### POST /v1/webhooks/vendor/accept

Headers:

```
x-scrapco-signature: <hmac>
```

Body:

```json
{
  "offerId": "uuid"
}
```

---

## 11. Idempotency

All mutating endpoints must support:

Header:

```
Idempotency-Key: uuid
```

Requests with same key must not create duplicate records.

---

## 12. Rate Limiting

Limits:

* Auth endpoints: strict
* Pickup creation: 10 per hour per user
* Webhooks: HMAC validated but rate limited

Redis-backed rate limiting required.

---

## 13. Error Codes

Standardized error codes:

* UNAUTHORIZED
* FORBIDDEN
* INVALID_INPUT
* NOT_FOUND
* OFFER_EXPIRED
* DUPLICATE_REQUEST
* INTERNAL_ERROR

No raw database errors returned.

---

## 14. API Guardrails

The API must:

* Never expose service-role key
* Never allow admin via env flag
* Never allow unauthenticated vendor updates
* Never allow state transitions out of order
* Never delete financial records

---

## 15. Summary

API layer is:

* Stateless
* Secure
* Role-aware
* Queue-integrated
* Versioned
* Idempotent
* Horizontally scalable

No polling-based design.
No in-memory dispatch logic.
All lifecycle changes logged.

